        <name>14.4.2.3 Exercise 2</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; Find the area of the surface generated when \(y ={@y@}\) in the interval \({@a@}\leq x \leq {@b@}\) is rotated about the \(x\)-axis. Give your answer in &lt;b&gt;exact&lt;/b&gt; form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The area is [[input:ans1]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[validation:ans1]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;Given \(y ={@y@}\) then \( \dfrac{\mathrm{d}y}{\mathrm{d}y}= \displaystyle {@dy@}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Using the formula \[\text{area}=\int_a^b 2\pi y \sqrt{1+\left(\frac{\mathrm{d}y}{\mathrm{d}x}\right)^2} \ \mathrm{d}x,\] the area of the surface generated is calculated to be: \[A = \int_{{@a@}}^{{@b@}} 2\pi ({@y@}) \sqrt{1+{@dy^2@}} \ \mathrm{d}x = \left[ {@I@} \right]_{{@a@}}^{{@b@}}= {@ta1@}.\]&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
